comment: Don't do it.

comment: I would recommend this class to other students. This class was great and was very well organized. Prof. E took the time to make sure instructions were clear and straight forward.
I loved this professor. They honestly wanted to ensure you understood the content and succeeded throughout the course. I would again.

I would recommend Professor Feinman! They were fantastic to have as a professor. No textbook was required, all readings were provided on Canvas. Also, to switch things up, Professor Feinman added films/videos to course material to engage topics learned during the course. Take this class!!
they are very cool and good
Very professional and has everything organized well.
Honestly the nicest Professor I have had in a while. She's very caring and makes the class easy for all students. lectures are fun and understandable. (her outfits are always sooooo cute!)

A professor worth taking and spending time with. She's not too hard of a grader and is pretty forgiving, however, you must try your best to pay attention to the lectures. I suggest note-taking as best as you can on the different paintings, remembering should come naturally then

Dr. Pilliod helped me out a lot, especially since I started out rough in the beginning. 

She has fun class trips, gives extra credit, really cares about her students and genuinely cares about us.

I took Machine Learning for my senior year. There were 4 assignments which were easy to do. One group project which was based on implementing a model that he discusses in class. We were also given the flexibility to choose our own models to run. The exam was very easy if you go through his slides and assignments. It's mostly a variation of them.
I took CS-514 AI as well as CS 554 ML and both were amazing courses. I highly recommend taking his classes.
Must take if you interested in Data Science and Machine Learning, I learned a lot from Prof. Dehzangi.

I took professor's Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence course. He taught it in an interesting and helpful way, and I liked how the curriculum was structured with both theoretical and practical applications.
Interesting class with easy learning and interaction

I took Dr. Dehzangi's Artificial Intelligence course, though it wasn't listed.
He makes complex material accessible with engaging methods, real-world examples, and clear explanations, creating an inclusive environment where students feel confident and learn well.
Easygoing and considerate. I learned a lot from this course.

Worst professor ive had, extremely tough grader with no regard for personal circumstances. Whole class is lecture and slide based, with average 50 slides covered every lecture. Too much information, too little time and no remorse from the professor.

The worst, avoid if you can at all costs!

comment: Professor Shah is maybe a little blunt at times but I thought that her grading was very fair and her style of teaching left me well-equipped to complete the homework and tests. Definitely expect some disapproving looks if no one in the class is willing to participate, however.
I am going to be straightforward and clear here. After the midterm exam, infront of the entire class, without hesitation, she stated that she "expected lower scores."
Professor Cat was amazing! She made learning the material enjoyable and interactive.

Best lab professor! Take her if you can over the others. She is a great lecturer who actually helps you understand the information. She understands the course is hard and tries to help by preparing you for the quizzes and practicals. She makes lab fun, interesting, and makes time fly by. Easy to approach also. I would take her again in a heartbeat!

Dr. Conroy gives really great lectures that set the foundation for later nursing courses. She knows her material really well and gives a lot of real world examples to help remember the information. As long as you do the readings, attend class, and take notes you will do well in her class.
Great lecturer's, she really knows her stuff! I would take her again!
His instructions don't make sense

The class is Info to Tech. Pretty easy, all he does is give assignments and teaches you how to use Microsoft office like excel, ppt, word, and access. Do the assignments give attendance and easy A. it is not a lecture class, more practical class.
Fast paced lectures that give lots of real work examples and keeps you engaged. Fair grading with exams. Really good with cardiac. I would take her again!

I had Dr. Andress for an adult med surg course. She is very knowledgeable and provides excellent lectures! I learned so much in her course. Would definitely take again.
He is a must take for International Business. Follow all instructions on assignments and it's an easy A. You won't regret it!!!!

He's a very nice man. I've talked to him outside of class and he just seems to be very well rounded. At least for the “Intro to Business” course, there isn't much work but when it comes to it; prepare to read and write. Very funny guy, down to earth, and a phenomenal speaker.

great!

comment: She's the Best Professor!! Course has assignments like LinkedIn Learning videos, weekly Reflection Journal posts of your thoughts, short videos to watch. comment:
Didn't pass, my fault though.

Pros: He's a kind professor who sent helpful emails, take-home quizzes, funny lectures and uploaded slides. The final was optional, and he encouraged office hours. 

Cons: no email replies, thick accent, fast talking, and no homework which meant failing one exam hurt. and was hard to recover. 

Overall I recommend!
four midterms, final optional, easy to lose focus in lectures, amazing teacher, easy to pass. should def take him, hes the best econ prof

Great Prof and all around nice guy. Created a safe space to explore the subject matter and collaborate with others. Highly recommend taking this class.

comment: She is an extremely fair grader who is available weekly for office hours if you have any questions or concerns.  One of the best professors I have ever taken a class with.

comment: Professor Lovett is very nice, joyful, and organized. Lovett goes based on everything that is presented in the syllabus and within the modules. She doesn't answer questions directly. She is still navigating Canvas so she doesn't post due dates for assignments. She does bring in candy.

comment: I had Nase for biochem in the fall semester of my freshman year. She is an amazing teacher that makes biochem easy and fun.
